The lemma states that the velocity of the trajectory is zero if and only if the norm of the position at time `t` equals `√(‖IC.x₀‖^2 + (‖IC.v₀‖/S.ω)^2)`.
-/

lemma trajectory_velocity_eq_zero_iff (IC : InitialConditions) (t : Time)
    (hx : IC.x₀ ≠ 0 ∨ IC.v₀ ≠ 0) :
    ∂ₜ (IC.trajectory S) t = 0 ↔
    ‖(IC.trajectory S) t‖ = √(‖IC.x₀‖^2 + (‖IC.v₀‖/S.ω)^2) := by
```

